    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-12-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886<gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss>.13/12–650:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d663fn1">Repeated to the Embassy in Cairo for Parker.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-12-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 18, 1950—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 359 Dec 6,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d663fn2">Not printed; Hare stressed the importance of the early
                        selection of a qualified currency expert for Saudi Arabia (886<gloss
                            target="#t_A1">A</gloss>.13/12–650).</note> 352 Dec 4,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d663fn3">Not printed; it relayed a request from the Ministry of
                        Finance for five American experts under Point Four—two experts for customs
                        organization, two to organize accounting procedures at the Ministry of
                        Finance, and one for currency and coinage questions (886<gloss
                            target="#t_A1">A</gloss>.00<gloss target="#t_TA1"
                        >TA</gloss>/12–450).</note> and previous tels same subj. Dept discussed subj
                    reference tels with Treas and Bureau of Budget. <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                        >SAG</gloss> request five experts approved in principle and prelim efforts
                    being made find personnel. To obtain final approval request and recruit
                    personnel, further info needed re terms of reference for experts. Dept believes
                    experts shld serve in advisory capacity and not assume responsibility execution
                    or admin their recommendation. Discuss above with <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                        >SAG</gloss> and transmit its and your comments Dept.</p>
                <p>Difficulty anticipated obtaining experts due scarcity technically competent
                    individuals plus doubts <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> will undertake
                    reforms which by nature require self-discipline. Another serious determent is
                    critical housing situation in <gloss target="#t_SA1">SA</gloss>. <gloss
                        target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> will be expected provide suitable living qtrs,
                    transportation and other facilities and necessary to obtain assurances they will
                    do so. Dept wld also appreciate <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>’s views re
                    feasibility of accountants and possibly their families living in Riyadh for
                    extended period in view unfavorable living conditions there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
